</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">2) Turn the system OFF via the main power switch 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Drain the cooling liquid: See: 
<xref keyref="06DISA004V2" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-FFE707FB-03C0-490F-8FEF-97228036917B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 06 How to drain the cooling liquid of the chiller unit (V2)?>06 How to drain the cooling liquid of the chiller unit (V2)</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Fill the system with water for flushing: 
</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Fill the chiller with Clean water, preferably demineralized water to the correct level (green zone) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><note id="GUID-44301C51-B938-4357-AA79-F166F8CD1B5A" class="- topic/note "/><p class="- topic/p ">The cooling liquid serves to prevent both corrosion and freezing within the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">While the system can operate with water alone, it is mandatory to use cooling liquid under normal conditions. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Turn on the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Once the chiller starts, it will raise the water temperature and circulate it through the system, effectively flushing it. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">6) When the printer is READY, shutdown the system and turn it off 
